<p>When the <code>:has()</code> selector comes to life this will be possible of course, but is there any way to select <code>&lt;select&gt;</code>'s with at least one option selected. Maybe using the <code>[value=""]</code> selector?</p>  <p>I wouldn't ask this if it wasn't because picking options changes the value of the select, so I think there may be a way through that path. Any ideas?</p>  <p>Example:</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="false"> <div class="snippet-code"> <pre class="snippet-code-css lang-css prettyprint-override"><code>.select[value] {   border: 2px solid red; }</code></pre> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;select multiple="multiple"&gt;   &lt;option&gt;value 1&lt;/option&gt;   &lt;option&gt;value 2&lt;/option&gt;   &lt;option&gt;value 3&lt;/option&gt; &lt;/select&gt;</code></pre> </div> </div> </p>